The program needs three arguments: train-data, test-data and amount of different classes.

It performs an Naive Bayes with Laplacian smoothing approach to classify the data.

This program was developed as part of the Artificial Intelligence course CS440 at the University of Illinois.

The original probelm set can be found at http://web.engr.illinois.edu/~slazebni/fall15/assignment3.html#text.


